               <p>MR. THOMAS BOYD. I am a <rs id="t18170917-47-viclabel234" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-47-victim342 t18170917-47-viclabel234"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-47-victim343 t18170917-47-viclabel234"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-47-victim345 t18170917-47-viclabel234"></join>, in partnership with Thomas Clark and Thomas French, we live in <placeName id="t18170917-47-crimeloc235">Skinner-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-47-crimeloc235" type="placeName" value="Skinner-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-47-crimeloc235" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-47-off232 t18170917-47-crimeloc235"></join>, the prisoner had been our <rs id="t18170917-47-deflabel236" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-47-defend340 t18170917-47-deflabel236"></join> for three years. Having missed some money, on the 10th of September, I marked two half-crowns and two shillings, and left them on the desk, about ten minutes after eight o'clock, leaving Ford in the counting-house; I returned again in a few minutes, with an officer, he searched the prisoner and found the two half-crowns and two shillings, which I had marked, on him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ADOLPHUS. It was not his duty to take the money up if he found it on the desk-the clerk was there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-47-person346">
                  WILLIAM 
                  FORD
               <interp inst="t18170917-47-person346" type="surname" value="FORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-47-person346" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-47-person346" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the clerk; I saw the money left on the desk, and also saw the prisoner come into the counting-house and go out again. I told Mr. Boyd.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-47-person347">
                  THOMAS 
                  WHITE
               <interp inst="t18170917-47-person347" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
